cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Inter‑Protocol QUIC Performance and Energy Benchmarking Dataset
abstract: This dataset documents a systematic inter‑protocol benchmark of seven QUIC
  reference implementations, measuring file transfer throughput, energy consumption,
  and data integrity across multiple bandwidth limits and file sizes. The methodology
  involved synchronized client–server runs on two nodes, with each run recording timestamps,
  SHA‑1 checksums, and power usage during the transfer. Evaluation scripts aggregated
  per‑run logs to compute goodput in megabits per second, compare hash consistency,
  and generate statistical summaries and visualizations for cross‑implementation analysis.
